# 🎨 Designs

> Module-level interfaces, state machines, and data models for the Agents Relay module.

---

## Designs

### D1 AgentInstance & Soul Rendering
**Status:** Implemented
**Module:** `crates/auto-forge/src/relay/agent.rs`
**Scope:** A2

**Interface:**
```rust
pub struct AgentInstance {
    pub id: String,
    pub profession: Profession,
    pub soul: SoulConfig,
    pub model: ModelConfig,
    pub context: AgentContext,
}

impl AgentInstance {
    /// Spawn a new agent for a pipeline step.
    /// Loads Soul from disk, resolves model config (with fallback chain).
    pub fn spawn(
        profession: &Profession,
        soul_id: &str,
        handoff: &HandoffDocument,
        specs: &SpecsDocument,
    ) -> Result<Self, AgentError>;

    /// Render the system prompt from Soul + Profession + context.
    pub fn render_system_prompt(&self) -> String;

    /// Render the user message from Handoff + relevant Specs.
    pub fn render_user_message(&self) -> Vec<ChatMessage>;

    /// Execute one turn of the ReAct loop.
    pub async fn turn(&mut self, tools: &[Box<dyn Tool>]) -> TurnResult;
}

pub struct SoulConfig {
    pub id: String,
    pub name: String,
    pub markdown: String,
    pub values: Vec<String>,
    pub handoff_ritual: String,
}

pub struct ModelConfig {
    pub provider: Provider,
    pub model: String,
    pub temperature: f32,
    pub max_tokens: u32,
    pub reasoning_budget: Option<u32>,
    pub fallback_chain: Vec<String>,
}

pub enum Provider {
    Anthropic,
    OpenAI,
    Local { url: String },
}
```

**State Machine:**
```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Unresolved: Soul ID provided
    Unresolved --> Resolved: Soul loaded from disk
    Resolved --> Ready: Model config validated
    Ready --> Thinking: Turn started
    Thinking --> ToolCall: LLM requests tool
    ToolCall --> Thinking: Tool result returned
    Thinking --> Complete: LLM finishes
    Thinking --> Error: API failure
    Error --> Ready: Fallback model activated
    Error --> Failed: Fallback exhausted
    Complete --> [*]
    Failed --> [*]
```

**Data Model:**
| Field | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | `String` | UUID for this agent instance |
| `profession.id` | `String` | Reference to Profession registry |
| `soul.id` | `String` | Reference to Soul config file |
| `model.provider` | `Provider` | API provider enum |
| `model.fallback_chain` | `Vec<String>` | Ordered list of alternative models |
| `context.budget_used` | `u64` | Tokens consumed this step |
| `context.turns_taken` | `u32` | Number of LLM turns this step |

**Depends on:** A2

---

### D2 PipelineEngine & Flow Execution
**Status:** InProgress
**Module:** `crates/auto-forge/src/relay/pipeline.rs`
**Scope:** A1

**Interface:**
```rust
pub struct PipelineEngine {
    pub flow: FlowSpec,
    pub current_step: usize,
    pub current_agent: Option<AgentInstance>,
    pub checkpoints: Vec<Checkpoint>,
    pub status: PipelineStatus,
    pub run_id: String,
}

impl PipelineEngine {
    /// Load a flow spec and initialize the pipeline.
    pub fn new(flow: FlowSpec, run_id: String) -> Self;

    /// Execute the next step in the flow.
    pub async fn execute_next(&mut self) -> StepResult;

    /// Pause the current run, saving checkpoint.
    pub async fn pause(&mut self) -> Result<Checkpoint, PipelineError>;

    /// Resume from a checkpoint.
    pub async fn resume(checkpoint: &Checkpoint) -> Result<Self, PipelineError>;

    /// Rollback to a previous checkpoint.
    pub async fn rollback(target: u64) -> Result<(), PipelineError>;

    /// Handle human approval/rejection at a gate.
    pub async fn resolve_gate(&mut self, decision: GateDecision) -> Result<(), PipelineError>;
}

pub enum PipelineStatus {
    Idle,
    Running { agent_id: String, started_at: u64 },
    WaitingForHuman { gate: Gate, since: u64 },
    Completed { result: CompletionResult },
    Failed { error: String, checkpoint: u64 },
    Paused { at_checkpoint: u64 },
}

pub enum StepResult {
    Handoff { to: String, checkpoint: Checkpoint },
    GateTriggered { gate: Gate },
    LoopBack { to: String, iteration: u32 },
    Complete,
    Error { message: String },
}
```

**State Machine:**
```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Idle: Flow loaded
    Idle --> Running: execute_next() called
    Running --> Running: Loop iteration
    Running --> WaitingForHuman: Gate triggered
    WaitingForHuman --> Running: Approved
    WaitingForHuman --> Running: Rejected (redraft)
    Running --> Paused: pause() called
    Paused --> Running: resume() called
    Running --> Completed: Final step done
    Running --> Failed: Unrecoverable error
    Failed --> Idle: reset
    Completed --> [*]
```

**Data Model:**
| Field | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `flow.id` | `String` | Flow specification identifier |
| `current_step` | `usize` | Index into flow.steps vector |
| `status` | `PipelineStatus` | Current state machine state |
| `checkpoints` | `Vec<Checkpoint>` | Ordered list of saved states |
| `run_id` | `String` | Unique run identifier |

**Algorithm (pseudocode):**
```
fn execute_next():
    step = flow.steps[current_step]
    profession = registry.get(&step.profession_id)
    
    // Gate check
    if step.gate == Human:
        status = WaitingForHuman { gate: step.gate }
        return StepResult::GateTriggered { gate }
    
    // Spawn agent
    agent = AgentInstance::spawn(profession, ...)
    status = Running { agent_id: agent.id, started_at: now() }
    
    // Run agent turn loop
    loop:
        result = agent.turn(filtered_tools)
        if result.is_handoff():
            checkpoint = create_checkpoint(agent, result)
            advance_step_or_loop()
            return StepResult::Handoff { to: next_profession, checkpoint }
        if result.is_budget_exceeded():
            return StepResult::Error { message: "Budget exceeded" }
        if agent.turns_taken >= step.max_turns:
            return StepResult::Error { message: "Max turns exceeded" }
```

**Depends on:** A1, D1

