### D4 Checkpoint Serialization
**Status:** Draft
**Module:** `crates/auto-forge/src/relay/checkpoint.rs`
**Scope:** A3, G4

**Interface:**
```rust
pub struct Checkpoint {
    pub id: u64,
    pub run_id: String,
    pub timestamp: u64,
    pub git_commit: Option<String>,
    pub git_diff: Option<String>,
    pub ledger_state: SpecsDocument,
    pub handoff: HandoffDocument,
    pub file_manifest: Vec<FileState>,
    pub token_usage: TokenUsage,
}

pub struct FileState {
    pub path: String,
    pub hash: String,  // SHA-256
    pub size: u64,
}

impl Checkpoint {
    /// Create checkpoint from current pipeline state.
    pub async fn create(engine: &PipelineEngine) -> Result<Self, CheckpointError>;

    /// Serialize to disk.
    pub fn save(&self, dir: &Path) -> Result<(), CheckpointError>;

    /// Load from disk.
    pub fn load(dir: &Path, checkpoint_id: u64) -> Result<Self, CheckpointError>;

    /// Restore file system state from checkpoint.
    pub async fn restore_files(&self, project_dir: &Path) -> Result<(), CheckpointError>;

    /// Restore git state.
    pub async fn restore_git(&self) -> Result<(), CheckpointError>;
}
```

**State Machine:**
```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Capturing: Handoff triggered
    Capturing --> GitSnapshot: File manifest built
    GitSnapshot --> LedgerSnapshot: Git commit or diff captured
    LedgerSnapshot --> Serializing: Ledger embedded
    Serializing --> Persisted: JSON written to disk
    Persisted --> [*]
```

**Data Model:**
| Field | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | `u64` | Monotonic within run |
| `git_commit` | `Option<String>` | Full SHA if auto-commit succeeded |
| `git_diff` | `Option<String>` | Patch if working tree was dirty |
| `ledger_state` | `SpecsDocument` | Deep copy of specs at this point |
| `file_manifest` | `Vec<FileState>` | Hash of every touched file |

**Depends on:** A3

---

### D5 TokenBudget Enforcement
**Status:** Implemented
**Module:** `crates/auto-forge/src/relay/budget.rs`
**Scope:** G5

**Interface:**
```rust
pub struct TokenBudget {
    pub limit: u64,
    pub warning_at: u64,
    pub strategy: BudgetStrategy,
}

pub enum BudgetStrategy {
    HardStop,
    EscalateModel,
    SummarizeContext,
    SkipOptional,
}

pub struct BudgetTracker {
    pub run_budget: TokenBudget,
    pub step_budgets: HashMap<String, TokenBudget>,
    pub cumulative: u64,
    pub per_step: HashMap<String, u64>,
}

impl BudgetTracker {
    /// Record token usage from an API response.
    pub fn record(&mut self, step: &str, input: u64, output: u64);

    /// Check if current spend triggers any budget action.
    pub fn check(&self, step: &str) -> BudgetAction;

    /// Estimate "parallel cost" for analytics.
    pub fn estimate_parallel_cost(&self, num_agents: u32, avg_context: u64) -> u64;
}

pub enum BudgetAction {
    None,
    Warning { remaining: u64 },
    Compress,
    HardStop,
}
```

**Data Model:**
| Field | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `limit` | `u64` | Hard token limit |
| `warning_at` | `u64` | Percentage (0-1) of limit where warning fires |
| `strategy` | `BudgetStrategy` | Action when limit reached |
| `cumulative` | `u64` | Total tokens this run |
| `per_step` | `HashMap` | Tokens per profession/step |

**Depends on:** G5
